  "slug": "multiseed-loaf",
  "title": "Multiseed loaf",
  "subtitle": "A yeasted sandwich loaf with five seeds throughout",
  "excerpt": "A reliably good everyday loaf with a mix of five seeds in the dough and scattered on the crust. Uses wholemeal and white flour for a slight nuttiness without the density of a 100% wholemeal loaf.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Original recipe. The multiseed loaf is a category of British everyday bread rather than a specific named dish; there is no single canonical source. The method follows standard yeasted tin-bread technique as documented across British baking literature.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A reliable everyday loaf with five seeds in the dough and on the crust. This version uses 350 g of strong white flour and 150 g of wholemeal, giving a slight nuttiness without the density of a full wholemeal loaf. Sunflower, pumpkin, sesame, poppy, and linseeds are the five used here, though any combination in similar proportions works.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The dough needs two rises. The crumb is slightly open but firm enough to slice and hold its shape under a thick spread of butter. Knead until the dough passes the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "windowpane test",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp6ko8ce0001lgv4mo3nq0hb"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": about eight to ten minutes by hand or six in a stand mixer.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ingredients",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "quantity": 350,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientSlug": "strong-bread-flour"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "quantity": 150,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientSlug": "wholemeal-bread-flour"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "quantity": 9,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": "one 7 g sachet",
              "quantity": 7,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientSlug": "yeast-dried"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "unit": "ml",
              "prepNote": null,
              "quantity": 20,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientSlug": "sunflower-oil"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": "plus extra to scatter on top",
              "quantity": 15,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientSlug": "poppy-seeds"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": "plus extra to scatter on top",
              "quantity": 20,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientSlug": "sesame-seeds"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and knead",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Dissolve {{yeast-dried}} in 325 ml of warm water and leave for two minutes. Combine {{strong-bread-flour}}, {{wholemeal-bread-flour}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} in a large bowl. Add the yeast water and {{sunflower-oil}} and mix to a rough dough.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Knead for eight to ten minutes by hand on a lightly floured surface, or six minutes on a stand mixer with the dough hook. The dough is ready when a small piece stretched between your fingers becomes translucent without tearing.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the seeds and bulk ferment, 75 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Flatten the dough on the worktop. Scatter {{poppy-seeds}} and {{sesame-seeds}} over it. Fold the dough over on itself a few times to work them in.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Shape into a ball, place in an oiled bowl, cover, and leave in a warm spot for about 75 minutes until doubled.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape and prove, 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Lightly oil a 900 g loaf tin. Turn the dough onto a floured surface and shape into an oblong: press flat, fold the two short sides inward, then roll tightly from the near long edge away from you.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Lower seam-side down into the tin. Scatter a little extra sesame and poppy seed on top and press gently into the surface. Cover loosely and prove for 30 minutes until the dough crowns 2 to 3 cm above the rim.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan (220°C conventional). An oven thermometer is useful here; a low oven gives a pale, soft crust.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until the crust is deep and evenly brown. Turn the loaf out of the tin; the sides and base should be firm and the base should sound hollow when tapped. Cool on a rack for at least 45 minutes before slicing.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Notes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Use any combination of seeds in the same total weight: linseed, pumpkin seeds, and sunflower seeds add more texture alongside sesame and poppy. Avoid very large seeds on the crust; they can burn before the loaf is baked through.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Adding 1 tablespoon of honey to the dough water gives a slightly sweeter flavour and a better shelf life; sugar is mildly hygroscopic.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "The loaf keeps well for three days wrapped in a cloth. Refrigeration dries it out faster.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
